entries.femaleVariant: Man, I'm never goin' back to the can, nuh-uh. Ain't happenin'. Gonna sober up, get my shit together, go back to the trailer park. Things are gonna be different, I can feel it!
Yeah, man, prison blows, buuuut it's got it's silver linings. Like, it's good to spend some time away from your girl, 'cause then after, like, she'll be aaaall over you.
And like, it's the same for dope, right? 'Cause when you take that first, sweet hit after a dry spell, it's like every cell in your brain is gettin' itself off at the same time.
Ya see that? That's the power of positive thinkin', right there. I read books on that shit, choom, about, like, seein' the good in the bad? But yeah, never goin' back to jail. Never.
Like, never ever. It's hard goin' through life without your daily fix, y'know?
I guess that's good, 'cause like, when you two were gone, I planted this whole field of danky cabbage, and like--
Hoooooly shit! You're a fuckin' genius!
We're gonna make a goddamn fortune! And then we'll, like, buy an island or some shit!
